WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:24.987 --> 00:00:27.900
I think I'm in love with Joon.

3
00:00:36.010 --> 00:00:39.902
I think I've finally met my soulmate.

4
00:01:15.687 --> 00:01:18.012
<i>[Episode 2]</i>
Joon.

5
00:01:18.012 --> 00:01:20.423
How can this food be so delicious?

6
00:01:20.423 --> 00:01:22.917
You know good food.
Do you want some more?

7
00:01:22.917 --> 00:01:24.602
500 won for an extra
bowl of rice, okay?

8
00:01:24.602 --> 00:01:26.539
- I'm in.
- Okay.

9
00:01:30.753 --> 00:01:35.114
This place with my soulmate and
my one and only childhood friend.

10
00:01:35.706 --> 00:01:38.176
This is my true paradise.

11
00:01:50.191 --> 00:01:52.527
You look really surprised.

12
00:01:52.527 --> 00:01:54.250
Did you lose something?

13
00:01:55.146 --> 00:01:59.795
Ah, thank you for letting me
stay over yesterday, friend.

14
00:01:59.795 --> 00:02:02.054
Would you like to eat with us?

15
00:02:02.479 --> 00:02:03.492
Friend?

16
00:02:04.640 --> 00:02:06.979
Why didn't you tell me
you were going up?

17
00:02:06.979 --> 00:02:09.417
You disappeared suddenly,
so I was looking for you.

18
00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:11.517
You two are still speaking
formally to each another?

19
00:02:11.517 --> 00:02:14.672
Oh, Jae Hoon here isn't very outgoing.

20
00:02:17.868 --> 00:02:21.774
You should put away your blankets if
I allowed you to stay the night.

21
00:02:21.774 --> 00:02:23.842
Of course, my friend.

22
00:02:23.842 --> 00:02:25.670
First, let me have some rice.

23
00:02:25.670 --> 00:02:28.469
Please tidy it up right now.

24
00:02:31.254 --> 00:02:34.522
Sure. I can do that, friend.

25
00:02:37.892 --> 00:02:41.219
Hey, did your chairman's son
cause trouble again?

26
00:02:41.927 --> 00:02:43.898
What is wrong with this guy?

27
00:02:43.898 --> 00:02:46.367
What is it? Which one is it?

28
00:02:46.367 --> 00:02:48.767
Hey, Kwon Jae Hoon. You're on TV now.

29
00:02:48.767 --> 00:02:49.827
Oh, it's this one.

30
00:02:49.827 --> 00:02:54.005
<i>The airplane disturbance case has
caused a great deal of controversy.</i>

31
00:02:54.005 --> 00:02:58.170
<i>Gangsu Group has yet to release
any official statement on the matter.</i>

32
00:02:58.170 --> 00:03:02.142
<i>At this time,
no formal charges have been made.</i>

33
00:03:02.142 --> 00:03:04.820
<i>People are lobbying
to have this case dismissed.</i>

34
00:03:05.761 --> 00:03:07.640
Lobbying to have the case dismissed?

35
00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:10.932
Joon, the thing is...

36
00:03:10.932 --> 00:03:14.589
I guess you'll be busy again taking
care this rich reckless troublemaker.

37
00:03:14.589 --> 00:03:17.860
<i>Reckless troublemaker?</i>

38
00:03:17.860 --> 00:03:19.529
<i>Why am I?</i>

39
00:03:19.529 --> 00:03:21.479
If he was born with
a silver spoon in his mouth

40
00:03:21.479 --> 00:03:23.428
he should be thankful and live quietly.

41
00:03:23.428 --> 00:03:26.040
Where does he get off acting
high and mighty with money?

42
00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:29.875
People like this need to be erased
from the world. They're just evil.

43
00:03:29.875 --> 00:03:34.393
If this guy were in front
of me now... he'd be dead.

44
00:03:35.239 --> 00:03:36.352
<i>[Right here.]</i>

45
00:03:37.159 --> 00:03:40.742
Then there's you,
who makes money protecting him...

46
00:03:40.742 --> 00:03:43.289
I'd like to call the stations
and give them a tip.

47
00:03:43.289 --> 00:03:47.612
I'll hold myself back
because I'm very busy with work.

48
00:03:47.612 --> 00:03:49.629
You can do it if you want.

49
00:03:49.629 --> 00:03:52.909
- What?
- Don't hold back. Do what you want.

50
00:03:54.123 --> 00:03:55.957
<i>Troublemaker.</i>

51
00:03:55.957 --> 00:03:59.380
<i>Troublemaker, troublemaker...</i>

52
00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:01.469
- Clean up your blankets.
- <i>Troublemaker...</i>

53
00:04:09.570 --> 00:04:10.922
<i>[Mom]</i>

54
00:04:13.655 --> 00:04:16.480
<i>[Mom]</i>

55
00:04:22.473 --> 00:04:24.403
I'm in despair.

56
00:04:24.403 --> 00:04:26.655
She called me a troublemaker.

57
00:04:26.655 --> 00:04:30.694
Not just reckless, but a troublemaker.

58
00:04:30.694 --> 00:04:33.468
How can she be so mistaken?

59
00:04:33.468 --> 00:04:39.372
This won't do. I need to fix this.

60
00:04:39.372 --> 00:04:42.643
I need to fix this terrible
misunderstanding between me and Joon.

61
00:04:42.643 --> 00:04:44.912
I have made a decision, my friend.

62
00:04:44.912 --> 00:04:47.153
- What decision?
- I'm going to go.

63
00:04:47.153 --> 00:04:53.316
I'll fix this confusing misunderstanding.

64
00:04:53.316 --> 00:04:56.415
Don't get involved, don't start trouble.

65
00:04:56.415 --> 00:05:00.787
Go back to the hotel
and stay there, you got it?

66
00:05:17.246 --> 00:05:21.460
No, I've finally met my destiny.

67
00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:24.528
I can't let her think
I'm this reckless troublemaker.

68
00:05:24.528 --> 00:05:28.977
I must prove to her
that I'm not an evil person.

69
00:05:44.499 --> 00:05:46.417
<i>[Gangsu Distribution: Byun Gang Ho]</i>
As for our home shopping site...

70
00:05:46.417 --> 00:05:48.814
we're being inundated
with negative comments.

71
00:05:48.814 --> 00:05:52.150
Of course, sales have gone down
in our mart and department stores.

72
00:05:52.150 --> 00:05:53.610
<i>[Gangsu Foreign Franchise: Byun Geum Hee]</i>
What's the point?

73
00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:56.338
Everyone is already
talking about a boycott.

74
00:05:56.338 --> 00:05:59.735
<i>[Gangsu Food Director: Seol Ki Hwan]</i>
If there is a boycott...

75
00:05:59.735 --> 00:06:01.735
it will hurt Gangsu Food the most.

76
00:06:02.759 --> 00:06:04.941
<i>[Gangsu Food President & Group CEO:
Byun Gang Su]</i>

77
00:06:04.941 --> 00:06:06.812
How are the stock prices?

78
00:06:07.953 --> 00:06:09.973
Of course, Gangsu Group's
stock has taken a hit.

79
00:06:09.973 --> 00:06:14.564
Distribution, foreign franchise, and
food have all gone down.

80
00:06:14.564 --> 00:06:18.787
We need to start focusing on morals
and family culture from now on, CEO.

81
00:06:18.787 --> 00:06:21.610
Why bother talking in circles?

82
00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:23.013
Brother.

83
00:06:23.013 --> 00:06:25.884
Please discipline your son.

84
00:06:25.884 --> 00:06:28.230
Why must we all suffer
because of your son?

85
00:06:28.230 --> 00:06:30.961
President Byun Geum Hee,
this is a professional setting.

86
00:06:30.961 --> 00:06:32.881
Please refrain from
inappropriate comments.

87
00:06:34.124 --> 00:06:37.453
How dare you lecture your aunt?

88
00:06:37.453 --> 00:06:40.461
Why don't you take better care of
your younger brother?

89
00:06:40.461 --> 00:06:41.749
Don't act up with me.

90
00:06:41.749 --> 00:06:45.391
Hey, hey. It's not the first time
Hyuk has caused trouble.

91
00:06:45.391 --> 00:06:47.612
Also, you should cut it out, Geum.

92
00:06:47.612 --> 00:06:49.420
How upset do you think
our older brother is?

93
00:06:49.420 --> 00:06:51.347
How can I cut it out?

94
00:06:51.347 --> 00:06:53.230
Our stock values have
plummeted overnight.

95
00:06:53.230 --> 00:06:55.840
Hey, is it just you? Is it just you?

96
00:06:55.840 --> 00:06:58.280
Who was whining all morning?

97
00:06:58.280 --> 00:07:00.307
Hey! You don't even own that much.

98
00:07:00.307 --> 00:07:02.095
What do you mean I don't own much?

99
00:07:10.687 --> 00:07:12.792
I asked to meet to come up with a plan.

100
00:07:12.792 --> 00:07:15.307
Did I ask to meet to have
an embarrassing family fight?

101
00:07:16.747 --> 00:07:19.158
Our stock prices are dropping.

102
00:07:19.158 --> 00:07:23.299
We'll need to come up with
some sort of countermeasure... a plan!

103
00:07:29.071 --> 00:07:31.201
I have a plan.

104
00:08:04.841 --> 00:08:06.249
He showed up.

105
00:08:07.309 --> 00:08:09.429
- What?
- He showed up.

106
00:08:09.429 --> 00:08:11.749
The airplane disturbance, the second son.

107
00:08:17.312 --> 00:08:19.939
Plan? What plan?

108
00:08:20.970 --> 00:08:23.240
What kind of plan could you have?

109
00:08:25.523 --> 00:08:26.730
I'll turn myself in.

110
00:08:33.706 --> 00:08:37.044
I'll turn myself in
and take my punishment.

111
00:08:37.044 --> 00:08:40.244
I'll make everything
that went wrong, right again.

112
00:08:40.244 --> 00:08:43.989
I'll explain the situation,
so that it doesn't hurt the company.

113
00:08:43.989 --> 00:08:46.379
I will explain it all.
Please leave it to me.

114
00:08:48.374 --> 00:08:50.135
Don't do it.

115
00:08:50.135 --> 00:08:51.154
Excuse me?

116
00:08:51.154 --> 00:08:53.851
I don't need you to turn
yourself in or anything.

117
00:08:55.355 --> 00:08:57.308
Just don't do a thing.

118
00:08:58.417 --> 00:09:00.062
But, Father...

119
00:09:05.157 --> 00:09:07.273
Who are you to explain anything?

120
00:09:07.273 --> 00:09:09.783
Who would believe anything you say?

121
00:09:09.783 --> 00:09:13.183
Don't say a single word
and don't do anything!

122
00:09:14.293 --> 00:09:17.812
Just do what I tell you to and
go shrivel up somewhere.

123
00:09:19.263 --> 00:09:21.196
Still, I caused the problem
and I should fix...

124
00:09:21.196 --> 00:09:22.364
You punk!

125
00:09:24.134 --> 00:09:27.072
That's right. You did cause the problem.

126
00:09:27.072 --> 00:09:30.984
The bigger problem is that it made
an issue for the whole company.

127
00:09:30.984 --> 00:09:34.544
All because of you,
our company's image was damaged.

128
00:09:34.544 --> 00:09:37.893
Do you know what kind
of loss that created?

129
00:09:37.893 --> 00:09:39.023
It's unfair for me too.

130
00:09:39.023 --> 00:09:40.385
Why, you little...

131
00:09:42.403 --> 00:09:46.092
Unfair? What could be unfair for you?

132
00:09:47.936 --> 00:09:51.556
You go around making trouble
without a single thought.

133
00:09:51.556 --> 00:09:53.635
What's unfair for you?

134
00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:55.504
You are the most useless punk.

135
00:09:55.504 --> 00:09:59.986
You are a punk who doesn't
know how to do anything!

136
00:10:08.023 --> 00:10:13.489
<i>All wounds are similar to flowers
and the radiance of flowers.</i>

137
00:10:13.489 --> 00:10:17.014
<i>The wounds that bleed...</i>

138
00:10:17.014 --> 00:10:19.176
<i>give off the fragrance of flowers.</i>

139
00:10:29.105 --> 00:10:32.370
<i>The heart of the person
pierced with the fragrance...</i>

140
00:10:32.370 --> 00:10:34.894
<i>has a large wound.</i>

141
00:10:36.134 --> 00:10:40.825
<i>From that wound,
there was a fragrance of flowers.</i>

142
00:10:42.207 --> 00:10:45.205
Die, you punk! Die!

143
00:10:45.205 --> 00:10:46.946
You little rascal.

144
00:10:49.403 --> 00:10:50.980
I ought to just...

145
00:10:53.192 --> 00:10:54.432
CEO Byun!

146
00:11:31.091 --> 00:11:33.124
Hide him away well.

147
00:11:33.124 --> 00:11:36.412
Put a collar on him or put him in a box!

148
00:11:38.384 --> 00:11:40.773
Make sure he can't get out.

149
00:11:40.773 --> 00:11:42.893
Make sure no one can see him.

150
00:11:55.182 --> 00:11:56.611
Goodness!

151
00:11:56.611 --> 00:11:57.893
Oh, seriously.

152
00:12:27.379 --> 00:12:30.354
My friend... Mon ami.

153
00:12:32.061 --> 00:12:33.677
My friend.

154
00:12:38.711 --> 00:12:40.124
Can you get up?

155
00:12:42.057 --> 00:12:43.313
Ow.

156
00:12:44.307 --> 00:12:46.374
Oh, this is nothing.

157
00:12:50.884 --> 00:12:52.354
You know my father?

158
00:12:53.572 --> 00:12:55.436
His fists have gotten much weaker.

159
00:12:59.148 --> 00:13:00.682
Maybe that's why...

160
00:13:02.124 --> 00:13:03.542
he's using his feet now.

161
00:13:25.744 --> 00:13:26.955
Hello.

162
00:13:26.955 --> 00:13:29.485
- Hello.
- Hello.

163
00:13:29.485 --> 00:13:31.193
Good morning.

164
00:13:38.669 --> 00:13:41.244
Did he go to help that rich troublemaker?

165
00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.966
<i>[Mom]</i>

166
00:14:03.664 --> 00:14:06.289
I told you to go to that hotel.
Why did you come here?

167
00:14:08.624 --> 00:14:12.970
I wanted to prove that I wasn't
just a reckless troublemaker.

168
00:14:12.970 --> 00:14:17.283
Chief Byun is doing what he can
to stop you from going to prison.

169
00:14:17.283 --> 00:14:21.268
He wants to buy time as long as
he can and end it with probation.

170
00:14:26.908 --> 00:14:28.451
Hyuk.

171
00:14:28.451 --> 00:14:31.893
There's a car waiting for you in
the parking garage, so go to the hotel.

172
00:14:31.893 --> 00:14:34.033
Don't get caught
by the reporters outside.

173
00:14:34.033 --> 00:14:35.311
In the end...

174
00:14:36.683 --> 00:14:39.371
am I someone who can't
do anything on my own?

175
00:14:42.221 --> 00:14:43.879
Take this.

176
00:14:43.879 --> 00:14:46.173
They might track
your phone, so turn it off.

177
00:14:55.051 --> 00:14:56.124
Let's go.

178
00:15:01.047 --> 00:15:02.826
Get out, get out, get out.

179
00:15:02.826 --> 00:15:04.277
I told you to go!

180
00:15:04.277 --> 00:15:06.518
Hurry up and get out!

181
00:15:06.518 --> 00:15:09.028
I told you, it's good for hangovers.

182
00:15:09.028 --> 00:15:11.177
You said it was good for stamina before.

183
00:15:11.177 --> 00:15:13.379
It's good for stamina and hangovers.

184
00:15:13.379 --> 00:15:14.961
I don't want it either way.

185
00:15:14.961 --> 00:15:17.566
I'm busy so get out. Go, go!

186
00:15:17.566 --> 00:15:21.431
If you don't want it, that's fine.
No need to be like this.

187
00:15:21.431 --> 00:15:24.192
Don't be this way.
Just try it for one month.

188
00:15:24.192 --> 00:15:26.706
I told you I don't want it.
Take it and get out!

189
00:15:26.706 --> 00:15:29.667
You drank all the free ones
I gave you to try last week.

190
00:15:29.667 --> 00:15:31.946
You enjoyed the free ones.

191
00:15:31.946 --> 00:15:34.239
Do you take me for a fool?

192
00:15:34.239 --> 00:15:37.836
Hey, Smoothie.
You forcefully gave them to me.

193
00:15:37.836 --> 00:15:40.633
Now, you're trying strong-arm me?

194
00:15:40.633 --> 00:15:42.052
- Section Chief.
- Seriously...

195
00:15:51.629 --> 00:15:53.465
It's fine if you don't want it.

196
00:15:53.465 --> 00:15:56.321
How could you throw it all on the ground?

197
00:15:56.321 --> 00:15:57.750
These are for drinking.

198
00:15:57.750 --> 00:16:00.263
Hey, Manager Kim! Call security.

199
00:16:00.263 --> 00:16:02.452
Get this woman out of here now.

200
00:16:02.452 --> 00:16:04.153
This is so annoying,
early in the morning.

201
00:16:10.971 --> 00:16:13.101
Ah, don't let it get to you.

202
00:16:13.101 --> 00:16:15.696
Don't let it get to you, Baek Joon.

203
00:16:19.047 --> 00:16:20.206
Hey, Hyuk.

204
00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:27.508
What do I with these?

205
00:16:31.033 --> 00:16:32.735
Oh, thank you.

206
00:16:39.068 --> 00:16:41.355
Oh, Hyuk!

207
00:16:41.355 --> 00:16:45.182
How... what are you doing here?

208
00:16:45.182 --> 00:16:46.340
Wait.

209
00:16:49.826 --> 00:16:52.068
Hey... huh?

210
00:16:52.068 --> 00:16:53.191
Oh...

211
00:17:07.799 --> 00:17:12.208
Gosh, seriously... who are you?

212
00:17:15.214 --> 00:17:16.505
Oh!

213
00:17:16.505 --> 00:17:19.734
Yes, that's right. Oh... it's me.

214
00:17:19.734 --> 00:17:22.604
How... how did you end up here?

215
00:17:22.604 --> 00:17:26.113
You don't need to know that.
Why don't you just drink it?

216
00:17:26.113 --> 00:17:27.783
How much could it cost in a month?

217
00:17:27.783 --> 00:17:32.981
For a person trying to make a living
and smiling while doing it...

218
00:17:32.981 --> 00:17:35.183
there's nothing
more important than health.

219
00:17:35.183 --> 00:17:38.340
Yes, yes! Ah, yes.

220
00:17:39.904 --> 00:17:42.204
If you really don't have
the money for it...

221
00:17:42.204 --> 00:17:44.840
talk to your team manager,
Kwon, about it.

222
00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:48.136
Yes, I understand.

223
00:17:48.136 --> 00:17:50.598
I'm sorry, Section Chief.

224
00:17:50.598 --> 00:17:53.273
Are you crazy? Let's go.

225
00:17:53.273 --> 00:17:54.754
I'm sorry.

226
00:17:54.754 --> 00:17:56.707
Joon!

227
00:17:56.707 --> 00:18:00.173
Hey, you! You, you... hey.

228
00:18:06.574 --> 00:18:11.434
<i>[CEO's troublemaker son,
Byun Hyuk, is in the office.]</i>

229
00:18:12.568 --> 00:18:14.171
<i>[CEO's troublemaker son,
Byun Hyuk, is in the office.]</i>

230
00:18:17.199 --> 00:18:20.513
Please don't post things like this
online, Section Chief Gong.

231
00:18:21.901 --> 00:18:24.081
The company atmosphere
is already quite hectic.

232
00:18:36.481 --> 00:18:39.289
What are you doing?

233
00:18:39.289 --> 00:18:42.229
We're trying to make sales,
not force them into it.

234
00:18:42.229 --> 00:18:43.490
What do you mean force?

235
00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:46.724
I was only trying to make him
understand as a human being.

236
00:18:46.724 --> 00:18:48.705
It looked like you were pressuring him.

237
00:18:48.705 --> 00:18:51.943
Anyway, that's not how you do sales.

238
00:18:53.985 --> 00:18:57.998
Hey... what's wrong with your face?

239
00:18:57.998 --> 00:19:00.150
- Did you get hit?
- Yeah.

240
00:19:03.293 --> 00:19:04.465
Just a bit.

241
00:19:04.465 --> 00:19:06.680
Tell me the truth.

242
00:19:06.680 --> 00:19:08.238
Why did you come here?

243
00:19:10.869 --> 00:19:12.475
The thing about that is, Joon...

244
00:19:12.475 --> 00:19:16.697
To tell you the truth,
my father works here.

245
00:19:16.697 --> 00:19:18.472
Where? Which department?

246
00:19:18.472 --> 00:19:22.407
Not any department in particular,
but the entire company really.

247
00:19:22.407 --> 00:19:25.313
- Is he a laborer?
- Huh?

248
00:19:25.313 --> 00:19:28.490
Like janitorial or security?

249
00:19:28.490 --> 00:19:30.166
- Security?
- Oh...

250
00:19:30.166 --> 00:19:32.507
So, he works in security.

251
00:19:34.049 --> 00:19:39.150
If you came to see your father,
why did you get hit like that?

252
00:19:39.150 --> 00:19:42.163
Oh, because of what happened yesterday...

253
00:19:42.163 --> 00:19:44.860
He got very angry because you got
fired from the hotel, right?

254
00:19:44.860 --> 00:19:46.541
- Huh?
- I see.

255
00:19:46.541 --> 00:19:49.111
It's not easy to get a job
like that these days.

256
00:19:49.111 --> 00:19:53.562
From your father's point of view,
I'm sure he's disappointed.

257
00:19:53.562 --> 00:19:57.361
How angry was he that he hit
his son's face like this?

258
00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:04.654
Well... I'm always the son
who disappoints him.

259
00:20:13.101 --> 00:20:14.769
Yes?

260
00:20:14.769 --> 00:20:16.810
You should get back to the hotel.

261
00:20:16.810 --> 00:20:18.875
All right.

262
00:20:18.875 --> 00:20:19.953
I will.

263
00:20:29.443 --> 00:20:31.747
I should get going.

264
00:20:31.747 --> 00:20:32.988
Thanks, Joon.

265
00:20:37.541 --> 00:20:39.598
- Hold on for now.
- What?

266
00:20:40.777 --> 00:20:43.244
The police might come around.

267
00:20:43.244 --> 00:20:45.538
It will be investigated
confidentially, so don't worry.

268
00:20:45.538 --> 00:20:47.850
I've already talked it over with them.

269
00:20:47.850 --> 00:20:52.650
By any chance... was this planned
by the prosecutor's office?

270
00:20:52.650 --> 00:20:55.710
We would be in trouble
if this came out too.

271
00:20:57.310 --> 00:20:59.031
Listen carefully.

272
00:20:59.031 --> 00:21:02.023
Since the media knows about it,
we need to make it look good.

273
00:21:02.023 --> 00:21:04.540
If the police find a case there,
it will have credibility.

274
00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:06.985
It will depend, but there
could be an official investigation.

275
00:21:06.985 --> 00:21:09.589
You have to make sure
that doesn't happen.

276
00:21:13.473 --> 00:21:14.763
You have him, right?

277
00:21:17.300 --> 00:21:19.570
Hide him well, so he doesn't get caught.

278
00:21:19.570 --> 00:21:21.242
We can't control it if he shows up.

279
00:21:21.242 --> 00:21:24.238
Gangsu Group is not
the problem. We will be dead.

280
00:21:24.238 --> 00:21:26.284
That's why it's not us, kid.

281
00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:32.579
Then I'll assume that's true
and get going.

282
00:21:32.579 --> 00:21:34.990
In my experience...

283
00:21:34.990 --> 00:21:37.209
these things are usually
from someone on the inside.

284
00:21:40.123 --> 00:21:42.358
Enemies are usually someone close by.

285
00:21:53.431 --> 00:21:56.871
Someone on the inside? What do you mean?

286
00:21:56.871 --> 00:22:01.714
Do you still have that
original file that I gave you?

287
00:22:01.714 --> 00:22:06.449
Of course, I put it in my safe
right after you gave it to me.

288
00:22:06.449 --> 00:22:08.698
I'm certain about it so don't worry.

289
00:22:08.698 --> 00:22:11.149
You should make sure that
that flight attendant stays quiet.

290
00:22:11.149 --> 00:22:15.231
It will really be a pain if she starts
giving interviews, crying and so on.

291
00:22:16.223 --> 00:22:17.402
I understand.

292
00:22:19.202 --> 00:22:22.063
Where is Hyuk now anyway?

293
00:22:25.614 --> 00:22:28.444
He's probably at the hotel.

294
00:22:35.666 --> 00:22:38.592
That's the new place
they're building. You see it?

295
00:22:38.592 --> 00:22:41.632
Today's the first day,
so they'll be carrying bricks.

296
00:22:41.632 --> 00:22:42.842
There's lots to do.

297
00:22:42.842 --> 00:22:44.396
- Don't worry. Let's go.
- Joon.

298
00:22:44.396 --> 00:22:46.127
- Oh, you're here.
- Joon!

299
00:22:46.127 --> 00:22:48.217
- Is this him?
- Yes.

300
00:22:48.217 --> 00:22:50.868
This is my friend, Byun Hyuk.

301
00:22:50.868 --> 00:22:53.883
He's going through a difficult time.
Please help him out.

302
00:22:53.883 --> 00:22:56.069
Joon, I don't know about this...

303
00:23:00.558 --> 00:23:02.954
He's a little soft. Will he be okay?

304
00:23:02.954 --> 00:23:05.507
What do you mean soft? It's all muscle.

305
00:23:08.567 --> 00:23:12.028
I know he's soft,
but he's got a lot of spirit.

306
00:23:12.028 --> 00:23:14.538
Please teach him well, okay?

307
00:23:14.538 --> 00:23:19.185
- Joon, must I do this?
- All right, since it's you asking.

308
00:23:19.185 --> 00:23:22.275
Hey, get over here Byun.

309
00:23:22.275 --> 00:23:24.044
What do you mean Byun?

310
00:23:24.044 --> 00:23:27.336
Yeah, what is that? Byun?

311
00:23:27.336 --> 00:23:29.836
Mister Byun, follow us.

312
00:23:31.989 --> 00:23:34.675
- Byun...
- Joon!

313
00:23:34.675 --> 00:23:36.197
You can make 90,000 won a day.

314
00:23:36.197 --> 00:23:38.185
It's hard to find a job like this.

315
00:23:38.185 --> 00:23:40.384
Don't complain, just learn the job.

316
00:23:40.384 --> 00:23:41.594
See you later.

317
00:23:45.406 --> 00:23:46.462
Joon!

318
00:23:47.675 --> 00:23:50.384
Why are you standing there?
Go work to earn your meal.

319
00:23:50.384 --> 00:23:52.344
Ma'am!

320
00:23:52.344 --> 00:23:53.904
Hurry.

321
00:23:53.904 --> 00:23:56.614
Hurry, hurry. Get going.

322
00:23:58.968 --> 00:24:02.093
You need to put more in there.

323
00:24:02.093 --> 00:24:03.384
Put more.

324
00:24:05.955 --> 00:24:07.111
Get going.

325
00:24:08.324 --> 00:24:11.062
All right. Let's go.

326
00:24:11.062 --> 00:24:13.442
You... you want me to carry this?

327
00:24:13.442 --> 00:24:15.109
Who else would do it?

328
00:24:15.109 --> 00:24:17.192
What are you doing? Hurry up.

329
00:24:18.492 --> 00:24:20.022
Okay. Go.

330
00:24:21.961 --> 00:24:24.175
All right. Go!

331
00:24:24.175 --> 00:24:25.504
Oh, oh. Wait.

332
00:24:25.504 --> 00:24:28.935
All right. Let's go!

333
00:24:30.738 --> 00:24:33.557
Mister Byun, hurry it up.

334
00:24:33.557 --> 00:24:34.904
Ouch.

335
00:24:44.170 --> 00:24:47.296
Hey, Byun. Get over here.

336
00:24:47.296 --> 00:24:48.335
I can't do it.

337
00:24:48.335 --> 00:24:49.581
What do you mean you can't?

338
00:24:49.581 --> 00:24:51.025
Byun Hyuk!

339
00:24:52.182 --> 00:24:54.365
Keep it up!

340
00:24:54.365 --> 00:24:56.057
Stay strong! Woohoo!

341
00:24:56.944 --> 00:24:58.086
Woo!

342
00:25:03.092 --> 00:25:05.743
Ah... I think I'm going crazy.

343
00:25:11.654 --> 00:25:12.775
Hello.

344
00:25:14.099 --> 00:25:17.454
Where are you?
Are you at the hotel?

345
00:25:17.454 --> 00:25:19.216
Jae Hoon, please save me.

346
00:25:19.216 --> 00:25:22.134
- What are you talking about?
- This is hell.

347
00:25:22.134 --> 00:25:25.029
I followed Joon and now I'm
trapped in a part-time job.

348
00:25:26.092 --> 00:25:28.149
What? Who did you follow?

349
00:25:28.149 --> 00:25:30.477
Why would you follow Joon?

350
00:25:30.477 --> 00:25:33.457
Please, Jae Hoon. Please save me.

351
00:25:33.457 --> 00:25:35.331
I'm scared and hungry.

352
00:25:35.331 --> 00:25:38.064
You rascal.

353
00:25:38.064 --> 00:25:40.173
Why are you hitting me?

354
00:25:40.173 --> 00:25:42.464
Hello... hello?

355
00:25:48.535 --> 00:25:50.362
He's not picking up.

356
00:25:54.427 --> 00:25:57.454
<i>This caller cannot take your call.</i>

357
00:26:01.358 --> 00:26:03.766
Hey, this is your life around here.

358
00:26:03.766 --> 00:26:05.478
You can't just take it off like that.

359
00:26:05.478 --> 00:26:06.836
Put it back on now.

360
00:26:06.836 --> 00:26:08.884
Why are you doing this to me, Mister?

361
00:26:08.884 --> 00:26:12.105
Why do you think?
I'm taking care of Joon's friend.

362
00:26:12.105 --> 00:26:14.312
You fool around every chance you get.

363
00:26:14.312 --> 00:26:15.440
Where's Joon?

364
00:26:15.440 --> 00:26:18.131
Where do you think?
She's working hard.

365
00:26:25.454 --> 00:26:27.354
<i>Oh my goodness.</i>

366
00:26:27.354 --> 00:26:29.194
<i>That enchanting figure.</i>

367
00:26:29.194 --> 00:26:31.602
<i>Every movement filled with passion.</i>

368
00:26:31.602 --> 00:26:34.763
<i>A natural grace waiting to explode.</i>

369
00:26:34.763 --> 00:26:36.454
<i>Oh, Joon.</i>

370
00:26:36.454 --> 00:26:38.705
<i>You are beautiful
no matter what you are doing.</i>

371
00:26:41.425 --> 00:26:45.025
Hey, hey, hey.
You're drooling.

372
00:26:45.025 --> 00:26:47.485
Wipe your drool and follow me.

373
00:26:47.485 --> 00:26:49.407
What are you doing?

374
00:26:49.407 --> 00:26:51.226
Have you seen the news?

375
00:26:51.226 --> 00:26:52.977
I came because of the video leak.

376
00:26:52.977 --> 00:26:54.114
Are you...

377
00:26:55.935 --> 00:26:57.927
suspicious of me right now?

378
00:26:57.927 --> 00:27:00.267
You just saw me get off the plane.

379
00:27:00.267 --> 00:27:01.736
I wasn't even in the country.

380
00:27:01.736 --> 00:27:04.365
You could've given it to someone else.

381
00:27:04.365 --> 00:27:08.378
You really are just too much.

382
00:27:08.378 --> 00:27:10.172
I'm the victim.

383
00:27:10.172 --> 00:27:14.066
You people didn't take care of it and
now you're coming to threaten the victim?

384
00:27:14.066 --> 00:27:17.326
I hope you understand why I would
have to come talk to you.

385
00:27:17.326 --> 00:27:19.098
I'm doing my best to forget it.

386
00:27:21.156 --> 00:27:24.246
If you continue to come
looking for me regarding this...

387
00:27:24.246 --> 00:27:27.826
I might forget about this settlement.

388
00:27:27.826 --> 00:27:31.408
I hope I don't need to see
your face in the future.

389
00:27:33.637 --> 00:27:36.037
Someone from the media might contact you.

390
00:27:43.659 --> 00:27:46.065
Don't ever agree to an interview.

391
00:27:46.065 --> 00:27:50.188
Keep this a secret from your co-workers
and the people around you.

392
00:27:50.188 --> 00:27:54.609
If you break the contract,
we can breach this settlement, as well.

393
00:27:54.609 --> 00:27:55.637
Goodbye.

394
00:28:12.755 --> 00:28:13.958
Good job.

395
00:28:15.737 --> 00:28:18.007
Good job, young man.

396
00:28:18.007 --> 00:28:19.182
Good work.

397
00:28:20.277 --> 00:28:22.580
You should put some
muscle-healing pads on him.

398
00:28:22.580 --> 00:28:24.307
You're the one who suffered, Mister.

399
00:28:24.307 --> 00:28:26.214
Yeah, I guess.

400
00:28:26.214 --> 00:28:28.821
Hey, you're a young man.

401
00:28:28.821 --> 00:28:31.983
You need more strength.

402
00:28:31.983 --> 00:28:33.671
- Goodbye.
- Yeah.

403
00:28:41.583 --> 00:28:44.899
Ta-da! Today's pay, 90,000 won.

404
00:28:47.665 --> 00:28:50.712
10,000 won is for the lunch
you had earlier.

405
00:28:50.712 --> 00:28:53.495
20,000 won is for the shovel
you broke today.

406
00:28:53.495 --> 00:28:56.592
For the ramen yesterday, I'll give you
a discount since you suffered.

407
00:28:56.592 --> 00:29:01.394
Breakfast was 4,500 won, and tomorrow's
breakfast will be 20,000 won.

408
00:29:01.394 --> 00:29:02.969
Here. Good work.

409
00:29:11.516 --> 00:29:12.762
40,000 won.

410
00:29:14.592 --> 00:29:16.312
Just to earn this...

411
00:29:42.108 --> 00:29:44.160
You don't need to call your dad?

412
00:29:45.698 --> 00:29:49.548
He must feel bad
after hitting you like that.

413
00:29:49.548 --> 00:29:51.606
I told you.

414
00:29:51.606 --> 00:29:55.609
No news is good news
when it comes to me and my father.

415
00:29:55.609 --> 00:29:58.345
I don't know what the issue is.

416
00:29:58.345 --> 00:30:00.969
You should still be good
to him while he's around.

417
00:30:00.969 --> 00:30:02.986
It'll be too late once he passes away.

418
00:30:05.540 --> 00:30:07.925
What was your father like?

419
00:30:09.006 --> 00:30:10.095
My dad?

420
00:30:15.380 --> 00:30:16.755
He was a normal man.

421
00:30:18.685 --> 00:30:22.125
He was kind and warm.

422
00:30:22.125 --> 00:30:25.727
He was loving and sensitive.

423
00:30:25.727 --> 00:30:28.110
So, my mom found him
a little bit frustrating.

424
00:30:28.110 --> 00:30:29.897
He was the best dad to me.

425
00:30:31.566 --> 00:30:33.719
If I think about it now...

426
00:30:33.719 --> 00:30:37.051
I think he got hurt by the world
a lot because he had so much love.

427
00:30:41.768 --> 00:30:43.910
- So, I...
- Wait, stop!

428
00:30:45.242 --> 00:30:46.359
What is it?

429
00:30:48.890 --> 00:30:52.340
You were about step on
the dandelion seed flower.

430
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:54.669
Wait.

431
00:30:55.069 --> 00:30:57.718
Here we go.

432
00:31:36.711 --> 00:31:40.609
Whenever I see the dandelion seeds,
I want to let them fly.

433
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:46.269
It's like a wounded soul
is flying free somewhere.

434
00:31:47.971 --> 00:31:52.310
If they can find root
somewhere new and live there...

435
00:31:52.310 --> 00:31:54.979
they can forget their past bad memories.

436
00:32:24.393 --> 00:32:25.742
Oh, Jae Hoon.

437
00:32:25.742 --> 00:32:28.362
Oh, my friend Jae Hoon.

438
00:32:30.042 --> 00:32:33.189
I guess he's coming home from work.

439
00:32:36.369 --> 00:32:39.239
What are you doing here?
You didn't go home?

440
00:32:39.239 --> 00:32:41.898
Oh, the thing is...

441
00:32:41.898 --> 00:32:45.739
He started working a job
with me today. 90,000 won a day.

442
00:32:45.739 --> 00:32:47.939
Yes, 90,000 won a day.

443
00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:51.219
So, that's why I want to ask...

444
00:32:51.219 --> 00:32:55.069
can he stay with you
until he gets his own place?

445
00:32:55.069 --> 00:32:56.848
Can I, Jae Hoon, my friend?

446
00:32:56.848 --> 00:33:00.228
No, just go back to where you belong.

447
00:33:00.228 --> 00:33:04.169
If you don't want to,
then he can stay at my place.

448
00:33:04.169 --> 00:33:05.813
- Really?
- Are you crazy?

449
00:33:05.813 --> 00:33:08.561
I can go sleep downstairs at my
friend's place on the third floor.

450
00:33:09.669 --> 00:33:12.420
But, it'll be 15,000 won a night.
What do you think?

451
00:33:12.420 --> 00:33:14.225
I'll pay for two nights.

452
00:33:19.771 --> 00:33:21.890
Sounds good.

453
00:33:21.890 --> 00:33:23.772
That's good.

454
00:33:23.772 --> 00:33:25.314
Let's go, Joon.

455
00:33:25.314 --> 00:33:26.709
Let's go!

456
00:33:29.377 --> 00:33:31.815
What? I paid already.

457
00:33:31.815 --> 00:33:34.965
What is your problem?
I'm going up to Joon's to sleep.

458
00:33:34.965 --> 00:33:36.887
I paid 30,000 won.

459
00:33:38.040 --> 00:33:39.040
Geez.

460
00:33:39.040 --> 00:33:41.852
Be quiet. Shut your mouth
and and go to bed here.

461
00:33:41.852 --> 00:33:44.271
Joon... Joon!

462
00:33:44.271 --> 00:33:45.960
- Joon!
- Hey.

463
00:33:45.960 --> 00:33:48.871
What? What? My 30,000 won.

464
00:33:51.589 --> 00:33:53.233
My 30,000 won.

465
00:33:54.160 --> 00:33:55.336
Joon.

466
00:33:56.429 --> 00:33:58.510
Joon!

467
00:34:08.053 --> 00:34:10.489
<i>[Mom]</i>

468
00:34:12.321 --> 00:34:14.089
<i>[Mom]</i>

469
00:34:17.297 --> 00:34:18.681
<i>[Mom]</i>

470
00:34:43.705 --> 00:34:46.937
<font color="#80ffff">[DF Ver] E02 Revolutionary Love ""</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">-= Ruo Xi =-</font>

471
00:35:09.732 --> 00:35:10.857
Oh my.

472
00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:14.420
Oh, you scared me.

473
00:35:16.266 --> 00:35:18.357
What is this? Ha Yeon Hee.

474
00:35:21.457 --> 00:35:22.605
It's me.

475
00:35:23.547 --> 00:35:25.672
Look at you just drinking
soju with no food.

476
00:35:26.817 --> 00:35:29.196
You should've called if you were here.

477
00:35:29.196 --> 00:35:30.960
It's not right of you
to drink without me.

478
00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:33.616
I wouldn't do that.

479
00:35:33.616 --> 00:35:36.857
This one is for our pretty Joon.

480
00:35:36.857 --> 00:35:38.882
Thank you very much.

481
00:35:40.408 --> 00:35:42.620
What is it? Something's wrong, huh?

482
00:35:43.696 --> 00:35:44.766
Joon.

483
00:35:46.245 --> 00:35:47.875
Have you seen the news?

484
00:35:48.757 --> 00:35:51.948
Third generation rich guy,
airplane disturbance.

485
00:35:53.821 --> 00:35:55.544
It can't be...

486
00:35:55.544 --> 00:35:58.199
That flight attendant
whose face is blurred out.

487
00:35:58.199 --> 00:36:00.462
That person is...

488
00:36:02.486 --> 00:36:03.728
me.

489
00:36:06.877 --> 00:36:08.368
What... what?

490
00:36:12.853 --> 00:36:14.198
My friend.

491
00:36:15.607 --> 00:36:17.009
You see this money here?

492
00:36:20.210 --> 00:36:23.161
It's the first money I earned
shedding blood and tears.

493
00:36:24.969 --> 00:36:28.966
I don't think I'll ever
be able to spend this.

494
00:36:30.149 --> 00:36:31.471
My lucky 10,000 won.

495
00:36:33.252 --> 00:36:35.245
I'll save it as a keepsake.

496
00:36:36.303 --> 00:36:39.281
Go ahead and do that.

497
00:36:39.281 --> 00:36:42.649
You won't ever have to do
hard labor to make money again.

498
00:36:43.799 --> 00:36:45.158
Do you know?

499
00:36:45.158 --> 00:36:50.928
Most people can't keep money
as a keepsake after earning it.

500
00:36:50.928 --> 00:36:54.435
They need to eat when they're hungry
and they need shelter to rest in.

501
00:36:54.435 --> 00:36:57.277
A life where income
and spending is equal.

502
00:37:02.545 --> 00:37:05.165
Yes! Hell Joseon.

503
00:37:05.165 --> 00:37:09.957
I feel like Neo,
who just took the red pill.

504
00:37:09.957 --> 00:37:12.116
What are you saying?

505
00:37:12.116 --> 00:37:15.045
The matrix I've been living in
has been shattered.

506
00:37:15.045 --> 00:37:19.734
The woman who gave me the drug
showing me the truth is my destiny.

507
00:37:19.734 --> 00:37:22.797
