00:55:45.377 --> 00:55:48.263
<i>[Mom]</i>

767
00:56:01.502 --> 00:56:02.779
It's me, Mom.

768
00:56:05.828 --> 00:56:07.579
Have two starting today.

769
00:56:07.579 --> 00:56:11.349
Shouldn't you do that, at least,
considering what you did to me?

770
00:56:11.349 --> 00:56:13.739
Otherwise, I might
really call the police.

771
00:56:21.427 --> 00:56:23.217
Let go of me.

772
00:56:30.018 --> 00:56:31.848
What are you planning to do?

773
00:56:31.848 --> 00:56:34.878
You're not really going
to the police, are you?

774
00:56:34.878 --> 00:56:37.708
Ah, I don't know.

775
00:56:37.708 --> 00:56:40.016
How much will you
give me if I stay quiet?

776
00:56:40.016 --> 00:56:42.105
I need some money quickly.

777
00:56:42.105 --> 00:56:43.556
Are you going to be this way?

778
00:56:43.556 --> 00:56:46.523
Because of that troublemaker
rich guy you work for

779
00:56:46.523 --> 00:56:49.878
I lost my hotel job and
things aren't so good for me.

780
00:56:49.878 --> 00:56:51.726
How much do you want to offer?

781
00:56:51.726 --> 00:56:54.186
How much do you want to offer
for me to keep my mouth shut?

782
00:56:56.179 --> 00:57:00.266
You should know there are many
other ways to do this.

783
00:57:01.884 --> 00:57:04.813
Oh, you're coming on strong.

784
00:57:04.813 --> 00:57:08.663
Why? Will you hurt me if I talk?

785
00:57:08.663 --> 00:57:11.179
Hey, you're not even the victim.

786
00:57:11.179 --> 00:57:13.643
She settled and accepted it.

787
00:57:13.643 --> 00:57:15.744
Do you think you have
the right to act like this?

788
00:57:15.744 --> 00:57:18.985
Social justice and
getting rid of corruption.

789
00:57:20.085 --> 00:57:22.835
I'm thinking I should cut off this
corruption while I can.

790
00:57:22.835 --> 00:57:25.324
I want to make this into a just country.

791
00:57:25.324 --> 00:57:26.683
What do you think?

792
00:57:28.748 --> 00:57:33.155
This is why people need
to walk a careful path.

793
00:57:33.155 --> 00:57:38.005
If employment status is unstable,
society will always act up and complain.

794
00:57:38.005 --> 00:57:40.815
That's the state you're in.

795
00:57:40.815 --> 00:57:42.083
That's correct.

796
00:57:42.083 --> 00:57:45.474
That's why I really
hate rich conglomerates.

797
00:57:45.474 --> 00:57:47.715
It's really funny if you think about it.

798
00:57:47.715 --> 00:57:52.706
Your chairman's son runs away and
society ends up with more power.

799
00:57:52.706 --> 00:57:55.764
The reporters are all waiting
in front of the company today too.

800
00:58:00.978 --> 00:58:02.021
Do you mean it?

801
00:58:02.021 --> 00:58:04.233
- What?
- Money.

802
00:58:04.233 --> 00:58:05.931
Do you really need it?

803
00:58:10.704 --> 00:58:13.192
You're not on the same side.

804
00:58:14.067 --> 00:58:15.163
What do you mean?

805
00:58:20.099 --> 00:58:23.271
He's not going to turn himself in
to the prosecutors, is he?

806
00:58:23.271 --> 00:58:24.996
It's not that he's surrendering himself.

807
00:58:24.996 --> 00:58:28.083
If it's not that, then what?

808
00:58:28.083 --> 00:58:30.137
What is it?

809
00:58:32.429 --> 00:58:33.889
What do you think?

810
00:58:36.424 --> 00:58:37.965
<i>In my experience...</i>

811
00:58:37.965 --> 00:58:40.088
<i>these things are usually
from someone on the inside.</i>

812
00:58:40.088 --> 00:58:42.985
Enemies are usually someone close by.

813
00:58:45.139 --> 00:58:47.485
Where is Hyuk now?

814
00:58:47.485 --> 00:58:50.125
Have you seen him before?

815
00:58:53.364 --> 00:58:57.728
He's the second son of Gangsu Group's
Byun Gang Su, Byun Hyuk.

816
00:58:57.728 --> 00:58:59.945
Do you know him?

817
00:58:59.945 --> 00:59:01.514
Ah, oh...

818
00:59:03.576 --> 00:59:08.011
We got a call that he caused a scene
here and got kicked out.

819
00:59:08.011 --> 00:59:12.951
How could you kick out
a VIP guest like that?

820
00:59:12.951 --> 00:59:15.719
If CEO Byun Gang Su finds out...

821
00:59:15.719 --> 00:59:19.574
that his son was chased out in that
manner, what do you think will happen?

822
00:59:19.574 --> 00:59:22.027
I... I'm sorry.

823
00:59:22.027 --> 00:59:26.587
Our hotel has never kicked anyone out.

824
00:59:26.587 --> 00:59:29.009
- You haven't?
- No. Never.

825
00:59:29.009 --> 00:59:33.958
That kind of unfortunate event
has never happened in our hotel.

826
00:59:33.958 --> 00:59:35.559
- Is that right?
- Of course.

827
00:59:43.070 --> 00:59:44.266
Hello.

828
00:59:48.219 --> 00:59:50.565
You know who I am now, right?

829
00:59:50.565 --> 00:59:52.358
Yes, of course.

830
01:00:06.056 --> 01:00:07.286
Hey, parking.

831
01:00:09.090 --> 01:00:10.681
The police may go looking for him.

832
01:00:10.681 --> 01:00:12.257
Hide him so he doesn't get caught.

833
01:00:12.257 --> 01:00:15.275
We can't fix it if he shows up now.

834
01:00:17.389 --> 01:00:19.246
Can I get a card for my room?

835
01:00:31.969 --> 01:00:34.766
Oh, that's a cool uniform.

836
01:00:34.766 --> 01:00:36.230
That's a great fit.

837
01:00:47.889 --> 01:00:49.764
<i>To his room!</i>

838
01:00:49.764 --> 01:00:50.840
Here you go.

839
01:00:52.047 --> 01:00:53.058
Thank you.

840
01:01:07.567 --> 01:01:10.293
Oops! Oh my, oh my.

841
01:01:10.293 --> 01:01:12.391
I'm so sorry. What can I do?

842
01:01:12.391 --> 01:01:14.478
- I'm sorry.
- This is nothing.

843
01:01:19.786 --> 01:01:22.895
Don't be like that. Just take it off.

844
01:01:22.895 --> 01:01:25.304
I can dry it for you.
It will only take 10 minutes.

845
01:01:25.304 --> 01:01:26.835
Exactly 10 minutes.

846
01:01:44.661 --> 01:01:47.257
I can't do that while I'm on duty.

847
01:01:47.257 --> 01:01:49.384
Goodbye, then.

848
01:01:49.384 --> 01:01:50.478
Excuse me.

849
01:01:52.476 --> 01:01:53.683
Excuse me...

850
01:02:49.101 --> 01:02:50.639
My sweet home.

851
01:02:52.969 --> 01:02:55.349
My sweet home. My sweet home.

852
01:03:34.858 --> 01:03:37.438
Home sweet home. Home sweet home.

853
01:03:41.304 --> 01:03:42.505
This is nice.

854
01:04:12.460 --> 01:04:15.460
Hey... what are you doing?

855
01:04:15.460 --> 01:04:18.050
Keep the car waiting downstairs.
I'll bring him out.

856
01:04:18.050 --> 01:04:19.777
We'll talk details later.

857
01:04:24.471 --> 01:04:28.521
I can't believe things
are over with Joon.

858
01:04:36.951 --> 01:04:38.382
Are you sad?

859
01:04:39.433 --> 01:04:40.652
I'm sad too.

860
01:04:46.786 --> 01:04:47.907
Is that Jae Hoon?

861
01:04:51.759 --> 01:04:54.212
<i>[My Friend, Jae Hoon]</i>

862
01:04:55.681 --> 01:04:57.842
- Yeah, Jae Hoon.
- Hurry up and open the door.

863
01:05:26.181 --> 01:05:29.434
I'm here for your
dry cleaning. Are you inside?

864
01:05:34.601 --> 01:05:36.192
<i>Don't say a word.</i>

865
01:05:46.891 --> 01:05:48.924
Joon, what's going on? Why are you here?

866
01:05:48.924 --> 01:05:50.398
Are you working here again?

867
01:05:50.398 --> 01:05:51.893
- Get inside.
- Inside?

868
01:05:51.893 --> 01:05:54.123
I don't have time to explain. Get inside.

869
01:05:54.123 --> 01:05:55.554
<i>The police are outside.</i>

870
01:05:55.554 --> 01:05:58.436
I think they know you're here.

871
01:05:58.436 --> 01:06:01.556
Joon, you're here to help me?

872
01:06:01.556 --> 01:06:05.110
So, you were worried
about me, weren't you?

873
01:06:05.110 --> 01:06:07.498
No, I'm here because of money.

874
01:06:07.498 --> 01:06:09.587
- Huh?
- What?

875
01:06:09.587 --> 01:06:12.030
<i>There's a girl?</i>

876
01:06:12.030 --> 01:06:17.223
To put it simply, Hyuk has the fortune
of the folk character, On Dal.

877
01:06:17.223 --> 01:06:18.657
That's what I'm saying.

878
01:06:18.657 --> 01:06:24.326
So, Hyuk needs to be with this
girl in order to become a great man.

879
01:06:24.326 --> 01:06:28.085
She's already close to him,
a girl like Pyung Gang.

880
01:06:28.085 --> 01:06:31.866
I think I'll charge five million won
to get you out. How about it?

881
01:06:35.552 --> 01:06:37.509
No? I'll leave if you don't want to.

882
01:06:45.078 --> 01:06:46.152
I'm in.

883
01:06:49.465 --> 01:06:50.588
What?

884
01:06:51.811 --> 01:06:53.889
I have a condition too though.

885
01:06:53.889 --> 01:06:55.529
What's the condition?

886
01:06:55.529 --> 01:07:00.197
Until I can go home...
will you stay by my side, Joon?

887
01:07:00.197 --> 01:07:02.146
- What?
- Hey.

888
01:07:02.146 --> 01:07:05.052
I have nowhere to go because
the police are following me.

889
01:07:05.052 --> 01:07:07.844
I have to be on the run for now.

890
01:07:07.844 --> 01:07:10.871
I think I'll be less scared
with you by my side.

891
01:07:10.871 --> 01:07:13.141
What kind of crazy things
are you saying?

892
01:07:13.141 --> 01:07:16.371
I'll pay you the average salary
of a Gangsu Group secretary.

893
01:07:18.244 --> 01:07:21.320
You'll work from the time
you wake up until you go to sleep.

894
01:07:21.320 --> 01:07:22.433
What do you think?

895
01:07:30.828 --> 01:07:32.273
Hey, are you insane?

896
01:07:32.273 --> 01:07:34.822
- Who are you...
- My work schedule...

897
01:07:34.822 --> 01:07:37.246
will be 9:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.

898
01:07:37.246 --> 01:07:39.092
- What?
- Okay.

899
01:07:39.092 --> 01:07:41.550
No personal conversation
and no personal chores.

900
01:07:41.550 --> 01:07:43.476
You are not allowed
to pretend we are friends.

901
01:07:44.802 --> 01:07:47.072
Isn't that kind of harsh?

902
01:07:47.072 --> 01:07:48.527
What? You don't like it?

903
01:07:51.608 --> 01:07:53.518
- I'm in.
- <i>Hey.</i>

904
01:07:53.518 --> 01:07:55.579
What are you two doing?

905
01:07:55.579 --> 01:07:57.648
Hello? Hello?

906
01:07:57.648 --> 01:08:00.259
- <i>Hello?</i>
- This is important. Can you be quiet?

907
01:08:00.259 --> 01:08:01.554
What did you say?

908
01:08:06.762 --> 01:08:11.087
Then is today our first day?

909
01:08:14.495 --> 01:08:16.120
Yes, day one.

910
01:08:17.164 --> 01:08:18.343
What? Day one?

911
01:08:28.565 --> 01:08:33.565
Subtitles by DramaFever

912
01:08:51.115 --> 01:08:54.557
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

913
01:08:54.557 --> 01:08:56.206
<i>Even if I needed money...</i>

914
01:08:56.206 --> 01:08:58.597
<i>What if I get arrested too?
I must be crazy.</i>

915
01:08:58.597 --> 01:09:00.294
<i>Mister Byun. You're back.</i>

916
01:09:00.294 --> 01:09:01.802
<i>The oldest son is normal.</i>

917
01:09:01.802 --> 01:09:04.309
<i>It was always the second son
who was the problem.</i>

918
01:09:04.309 --> 01:09:07.446
<i>I heard you were in charge of him.
Where is Byun Hyuk now?</i>

919
01:09:07.446 --> 01:09:09.420
<i>What kind of person is like that?</i>

920
01:09:10.856 --> 01:09:12.228
<i>He looks very elegant.</i>

921
01:09:12.228 --> 01:09:13.669
<i>Is that Joon's boyfriend?</i>

922
01:09:13.669 --> 01:09:16.045
<i>How much do you need?
Tell me. I'll lend it to you.</i>

923
01:09:16.045 --> 01:09:17.356
<i>Forget it. Let's end it with this.</i>

924
01:09:17.356 --> 01:09:18.980
<i>Let's go down our own paths now.</i>

925
01:09:18.980 --> 01:09:20.959
<i>Why does everything I do
end up like this?</i>

